\begin{abstract}
  We propose and demonstrate experimentally a scheme to create entangled
  history states of the Greenberger-Horne-Zeilinger (GHZ) type. In our experiment, the polarization states of a single photon at
  three different times are prepared as a GHZ entangled history state. We define a GHZ functional
  which attains a maximum value $1$ on the ideal GHZ entangled history state and is bounded above by $1/16$
  for any three-time history state lacking tripartite entanglement. We have measured the GHZ functional
  on a state we have prepared experimentally, yielding a value of $0.656\pm 0.005$,  clearly demonstrating the contribution of entangled histories.

\end{abstract}

